<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1861-08-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1861-08-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="296" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d296">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Seward</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Harvey</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 8.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of
                                    State</hi>,<lb/><placeName><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1861-08-24"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 24, 1861</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch No. 8, dated July 30, has
                            been received, and I have the pleasure of informing you that the
                            President entirely approves of your diligent and judicious action
                            concerning the proposed proclamation of the government of Portugal. We
                            look with much confidence for good results from it.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer><signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">James E. Harvey</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c., Lisbon</hi>.</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>